data.title: VIEW RESULTS ON AUG. 20: Miami-Dade County Primary Election
data.meta_description: In addition to selecting a candidate from each party for two U.S. Senate races, Miami-Dade County voters will be selecting their choices for U.S. representatives from numerous districts, as well as selecting their choice for Miami-Dade sheriff – a newly created elected position in the county.
data.text:
Published: August 8, 2024 at 12:57 PMUpdated: August 8, 2024 at 9:18 PM

MIAMI-DADE COUNTY, Fla. – The Primary Election will be held on Tuesday, Aug. 20.

In addition to selecting a candidate from each party for two U.S. Senate races, Miami-Dade County voters will be selecting their choices for U.S. representatives from numerous districts, as well as selecting their choice for Miami-Dade sheriff – a newly created elected position in the county.

The winners from each major political party will face off in November.

Mayoral races are also being held for Miami-Dade County, as well as in Miami Gardens.

Candidates in both races need 50 percent of the vote to win, otherwise a runoff between the top two candidates will be held in November.

Incumbent Miami-Dade County Mayor Daniella Levine Cava and incumbent Miami Gardens Mayor Rodney Harris are hoping to hold on to their seats.
